# Truxe Dual License

Copyright (c) 2025 Wundam LLC. All rights reserved.

Truxe is licensed under a dual-license model:

## Community Edition (MIT License)

The Community Edition includes core authentication features and is licensed under the MIT License.

**Included Features:**
- Magic Link Authentication
- Password Authentication
- Basic OAuth Consumer (Google, GitHub)
- Basic Sessions
- Basic Organizations
- Basic RBAC
- Basic API

See [LICENSE-MIT](LICENSE-MIT) for full license text.

## Professional/Enterprise Edition (Business Source License 1.1)

The Professional and Enterprise Editions include advanced features and are licensed under the Business Source License 1.1 (BSL).

**Additional Features:**
- OAuth Provider (Login with Truxe)
- Passkeys/WebAuthn
- SAML SSO
- SCIM Directory Sync
- Advanced RBAC
- Advanced Security (Threat Detection, Anomaly Detection)
- Admin Dashboard
- React Component Library (@truxe/react)
- JavaScript SDK (@truxe/js)
- Priority Support

See [LICENSE-BSL](LICENSE-BSL) for full license text.

### BSL Key Terms

**Production Use License:** Professional ($79/month) or Enterprise ($499/month)

**Development & Evaluation:** FREE - Test, develop, and evaluate without any licensing fees.

**Change Date:** January 1, 2029 (4 years from first production release)

**Change License:** MIT License - After the Change Date, the Professional/Enterprise Edition will automatically convert to MIT License.

## Choosing Your License

- **For development, testing, or evaluation:** FREE (both editions)
- **For production use (self-hosted):** $79/month (Professional) or $499/month (Enterprise)
- **For managed cloud hosting:** Truxe Cloud (coming soon)
- **To resell or offer as a service:** Contact sales@wundam.com for authorization

